subject_prompt_600:
Sportfreunde Stiller is a German film actor and former professional footballer. Since the early 1970s, he played for several top German football teams and achieved success on the European stage playing with clubs like Bayern Munich and Stuttgart. He became famous because of his ability to create an "unpredictable" style which was very similar in all his appearances.

He then played for other top football clubs including Eintracht Frankfurt and 1860 Munich. As well as winning many awards, he also had an impressive career playing for his national side, Germany. In 2009, he retired from football. The only player to play a full season (2 months) for the National Team, Stiller made 6 appearances, scoring 2 goals, and his last appearance was on 23rd March 2010.

Rüdiger Linhof is a German football legend who is one of Europe's most successful footballers. Born in 1936, Linhof played for numerous clubs in Italy and Germany. However, it was under his tutelage at Schalke that he established himself as an international player and won many awards including 3 UEFA Cups with the club.

Linhof was a forward/midfielder who could always be found within Schalke's first eleven squads. He spent his entire career there and was the first and only Bundesliga player to win the Ballon d'Or on 4 occasions. After leaving Schalke, Linhof was the leading scorer at Real Madrid, scoring 102 league goals during his time there. After retiring, he went to FC Twente where he played a key role in the team reaching the Champions League final in 2005 with a game to spare. He went on to play for AC Milan until 2008 when he joined Inter Milan. He retired on 17th January 2016 after having been with the Italian club since 2000.
